comment: 'This type of dog is very smart! But you need to train him, try having someone dress up and scare you and you'll see how he protects you.'
'Look how his paws move when he runs!' (laughing)
So pretty, there are so many dogs that look like him on this street
A man tried to pet him but he flinched, so I explained that he's scared of men: 'Maybe he was mistreated'
Same flinching happened when a man tried to pet him: 'He must've had a hard street life, you have to give him time to adjust'
First time riding with a stranger in the elevator: the janitor asked his name
'Look at the stare!' Benji was crouching down in a 'stalking his prey'-like position
'So cute! My ex got me this dog, but he never took her out of the house so now she needs to get used to socializing'
'So cute!' (random guy reaching down to pet him)
You've got to behave for your mom!
'So cute! Is he a puppy?'
I explained to a man in the elevator that he gets nervous around people in the elevator
'Where are you headed? You should come to the park, a lot of us meet there after work every day'
'Look he's shaking he's so nervous!' He actually seemed very happy to me
Woman encouraged Benji to get in the elevator because she saw he was nervous
Same woman: 'You're going to have more fun than me! I'm just going to do laundry'
'He's a puppy right? Don't worry about my dog, he's timid'
'He's a puppy right? You can tell. Mine is a grandma'
After barking at another dog and then barking at a man: 'Why are you so angry?' This only made him angrier
After a Benji barked at a guy crouching down: 'Why'd you do that? I didn't do anything to you'
I said sorry to a guy when the elevator opened because Benji barked at him
I said sorry to a girl who Benji barked at
Benji observed a dog but didn't approach: 'See that's love at first sight!' Then we had a conversation with women about adopting our dogs, and how both are scared of men
'He's not neutered, he's going to keep peeing everywhere'
